1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:15,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:43,000
[Episode 15]

4
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,870
When you told me to
quit the publishing house

5
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:47,590
and focus on surviving,

6
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,789
I didn't listen to you as well.

7
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:52,070
Yeah, since when have you
ever listened to me?

8
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:55,550
[Oh no.]

9
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:57,430
[That's what Mr Fox had said before.]

10
00:01:58,430 --> 00:02:00,509
Since when have I told you that?

11
00:02:00,509 --> 00:02:01,750
We were strangers

12
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:03,259
before you came into the industry, right?

13
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,110
If we knew each other before,

14
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:07,910
I would've told you to give up
being an editor.

15
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,710
Look at you right now.

16
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:11,550
You can't even afford to pay a fine.

17
00:02:12,790 --> 00:02:13,870
Who would've thought that

18
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:15,990
the wealthy Mr Zhou Chuan

19
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:18,670
would hold it against me
for a meagre fine?

20
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:20,350
There's hot water in the pot.

21
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:21,390
Why are you drinking cold water?

22
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:36,470
Hello, Sister?

23
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:38,630
You've returned home?

24
00:02:40,020 --> 00:02:42,190
We can talk about Huang Quan Inn later.

25
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:43,980
You can go and annoy your Jiang Yu Cheng.

26
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:44,990
I'll hang up now. Goodbye.

27
00:03:00,790 --> 00:03:01,990
You should return now.

28
00:03:01,990 --> 00:03:03,150
It's been tough on you.

29
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:04,190
I've wasted two hours

30
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,150
of your writing time.

31
00:03:05,510 --> 00:03:07,030
How could it be a waste of my time

32
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,390
when I'm together with you?

33
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,670
I read the ending you wrote
while I was on the plane.

34
00:03:13,670 --> 00:03:15,150
You need to change it according to
what we've discussed.

35
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:15,870
Let me carry it.

36
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:17,630
Sister, I know now.

37
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:18,590
After I'm done helping you out,

38
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:19,710
I'll return and write immediately.

39
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,910
Don't worry, I won't lose.

40
00:03:48,450 --> 00:03:54,990
♫ They say strange things
and keep rapport ♫

41
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:51,510
[Our life isn't comprised of
our previous burdens.]

42
00:03:51,510 --> 00:03:54,750
[Our journey ends here.]

43
00:03:55,829 --> 00:04:02,730
♫ Guileless adults are reduced to a joke ♫

44
00:03:57,260 --> 00:03:58,020
Sister,

45
00:03:58,579 --> 00:04:00,660
I've put your things into your room.

46
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:09,830
♫ Unceasingly, here to stay ♫

47
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:17,350
♫ No dancing on the roof, but rain ♫

48
00:04:18,350 --> 00:04:25,310
♫ The loneliness has found
a place and moved out ♫

49
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:32,800
♫ Guests sillier than me
argue and exaggerate ♫

50
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:40,360
♫ The moon is
outrageously beautiful tonight ♫

51
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:34,780
Here you go.

52
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:37,510
We used them as our bookmarks
when we were young, right?

53
00:04:39,590 --> 00:04:41,150
That's what a girl would do.

54
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:47,080
♫ Lend me the light on your face ♫

55
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:44,270
You don't like it?

56
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:47,670
Forget about it then. I thought
it could serve as a memento.

57
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:55,320
♫ I've been giddy from drifting
in a sea of people ♫

58
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:48,790
Just throw it away if you don't like it.

59
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:56,220
I do like it.

60
00:04:55,490 --> 00:05:02,930
♫ Unwilling to admit my anticipation
of getting submitted to gentleness ♫

61
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,950
What do you like?

62
00:05:01,590 --> 00:05:02,909
I like ginkgos.

63
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:10,390
♫ I want to be led by you,
albeit a meager freedom ♫

64
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,580
I like ginkgos as well.

65
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:07,950
I like you as well.

66
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:17,400
♫ The Hand of the Creator
has finally seen to ♫

67
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:25,500
♫ I'm drifting in a sea of people.
And will frequently look back♫

68
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:32,960
♫ Scared to reach out my hand
that no one will save me ♫

69
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:40,290
♫ How rich can concrete skyscrapers be ♫

70
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:39,550
Sister.

71
00:05:39,909 --> 00:05:41,550
Sister, what's wrong with you?

72
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:44,440
♫ You are a rare shining oasis ♫

73
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:57,470
♫ Exactly what I want ♫

74
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,150
Do you know the meaning of

75
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:52,510
love comes upon once in your life?

76
00:05:58,790 --> 00:06:01,030
I've thought about it many times.

77
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:04,390
One day, when I'm old,

78
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:08,910
there's someone who would
still hold my hand.

79
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:12,470
We would take a walk in the park together.

80
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:15,630
As the breeze passes by us,

81
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:16,830
the sun

82
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:19,990
will shine on us.

83
00:06:19,990 --> 00:06:22,310
Birds will chirp on the trees.

84
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:27,590
No matter how many times I think about it,

85
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:31,030
Jiang Yu Cheng was always
the one on my mind.

86
00:06:34,260 --> 00:06:36,030
He will still make you sad.

87
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,590
I know that.

88
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:43,030
But I don't know how to give up

89
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:46,350
on that idealistic image of mine.

90
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:54,990
Sister.

91
00:06:59,550 --> 00:07:00,830
Go back now.

92
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:02,390
I want to be alone.

93
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:39,790
I have something to discuss with you.

94
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:42,030
We need to determine who will cook
and who will do the work.

95
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:44,630
Why don't you determine who will cook
and who will eat the food?

96
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,750
You're the one eating.

97
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:46,830
That's a given.

98
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:51,380
Do you think this is enough?

99
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:53,470
That's too much.

100
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:54,390
You can wash

101
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:56,460
all of our cooking utensils
with that amount.

102
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:10,030
Do you even know how to wash dishes?

103
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:10,980
Use this.

104
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:12,950
The metal sponge is used to clean pots.

105
00:08:13,590 --> 00:08:15,430
Isn't all of it the same?

106
00:08:19,590 --> 00:08:20,540
Mr Zhou Chuan,

107
00:08:21,790 --> 00:08:23,270
do you have a smurf account?

108
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:25,790
[Here she comes again.]

109
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:28,030
What smurf account?

110
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:30,780
I don't even have enough time
to handle my main account.

111
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:34,510
I haven't told you what kind of
smurf account I'm talking about.

112
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:36,030
I don't have any smurf account.

113
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:38,549
Weibo, WeChat, QQ, none of them.

114
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:40,830
Why are you asking me this?

115
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,950
Nothing. It's just a random question.

116
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:51,900
Mr Zhou Chuan,

117
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,540
I discovered something interesting.

118
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:58,230
What is it?

119
00:08:58,230 --> 00:08:59,750
For every ending of your story,

120
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,670
you'll put five ellipses at the back.

121
00:09:01,670 --> 00:09:03,070
Is that a habit of yours?

122
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:04,870
Can't I do so?

123
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:08,190
Of course you can. It's just that

124
00:09:08,190 --> 00:09:11,190
one of my online friend
has the same habit as you.

125
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,430
Plenty of people
have the same habit, you know?

126
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:15,550
So, are all of them your online friends?

127
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:17,510
But even the tone you're using
is the same as him.

128
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:19,420
Especially when
you're criticizing Mr Jiang.

129
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,620
He's bothering Jiang Yu Cheng as well?

130
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:23,820
You can introduce him to me then.

131
00:09:25,460 --> 00:09:27,270
What exactly are you trying to say?

132
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:35,350
Mr Zhou Chuan,

133
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:38,870
you're Mr Fox, right?

134
00:09:44,590 --> 00:09:45,790
Mr Fox?

135
00:09:49,270 --> 00:09:50,310
Who is it?

136
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,300
It's the Little Zhou Chuan
I've told you about.

137
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:57,230
You mean the one who's just like me?

138
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,630
You must be delusional.

139
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:01,270
You're saying that I'm Mr Fox
just because of the way I write?

140
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:02,710
Not just that,

141
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:04,630
the way you criticize people

142
00:10:04,630 --> 00:10:05,910
is exactly the same as him.

143
00:10:05,910 --> 00:10:08,350
You two are curious about
the same thing as well.

144
00:10:08,350 --> 00:10:09,700
Just like

145
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:11,020
the entries for the
Interactive Cultural Festival.

146
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:13,430
Now, you're using the tone
of my writing as evidence?

147
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:15,990
You should listen to yourself.
It's absurd.

148
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,510
I'm one of the authors for
the Interactive Cultural Festival.

149
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:18,430
Isn't it normal for me

150
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,990
to care about the amount of entries?

151
00:10:20,470 --> 00:10:22,550
As for that Mr Fox,

152
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:25,540
I think he's curious because

153
00:10:25,540 --> 00:10:27,070
he's one of my readers.

154
00:10:32,390 --> 00:10:33,870
You can call Mr Fox right now.

155
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:35,070
Ask him if he is me.

156
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:46,430
[Please don't make the call.]

157
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:47,590
[Please.]

158
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:52,270
[Please.]

159
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:53,870
Mr Zhou Chuan,

160
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:56,670
are you not Mr Fox?

161
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:59,350
Didn't I give you a chance
to prove it to me?

162
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:02,950
Forget about it.
I'll take it as a no then.

163
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:04,380
I won't dwell on this anymore.

164
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:06,830
[What a relief.]

165
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,420
I have to endure this every day?

166
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,270
My heart won't be able to take it
any longer.

167
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:17,950
Why are you staring at me?

168
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:20,100
Of course I can't admit that I'm Mr Fox.

169
00:11:20,390 --> 00:11:22,070
I wasn't honest with her from the start.

170
00:11:22,070 --> 00:11:24,620
What should I do if she knew that

171
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:26,390
I was trying to get information from her?

172
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:30,230
Mr Fox is me at my geekiest moment.

173
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:31,780
If she knew that I was Mr Fox,

174
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:32,830
what if she threatens me

175
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:33,630
and wants me

176
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:35,190
to hand over my copyright to her?

177
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:38,910
Enough already.

178
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:40,630
I know she won't resort to this.

179
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,750
But I'm sure she'll tease me for it.

180
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:44,980
I can imagine her face

181
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:46,350
when she teases me.

182
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:48,350
"Mr Zhou Chuan."

183
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:49,430
"I didn't expect you

184
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:51,070
to be such an emotional teen in the past."

185
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:58,110
What if she threatens me with that

186
00:11:58,110 --> 00:11:59,500
and doesn't want to cook for us?

187
00:12:00,590 --> 00:12:01,950
I'm fine with that.

188
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:03,670
But can you change from

189
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:05,220
eating freshly made dishes
to dried dog food?

190
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:08,470
That's why.

191
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:10,790
I can't admit it for your sake.

192
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:15,430
Let's not dwell on it anymore.

193
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:17,190
I will never admit that I'm Mr Fox.

194
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:18,190
Let's go.

195
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:19,470
Let's go.

196
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:27,370
[Moonlight]

197
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,350
Good morning, Mr Jiang.

198
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:32,620
Morning.

199
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:34,790
Are you here for the latest issue
of Moonlight Magazine?

200
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:35,390
Yes.

201
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:38,110
Count this as my present for you.

202
00:12:38,310 --> 00:12:40,100
Thank you.

203
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:44,230
Compared with the fan fictions
on Xin Dun Creative Exchange,

204
00:12:44,230 --> 00:12:45,820
seems like this issue's
Interactive Cultural Festival

205
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,070
focuses more on

206
00:12:47,070 --> 00:12:48,710
promoting new authors.

207
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:50,470
I guess all of the articles
are specially chosen.

208
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:53,070
That's what Mr Xia thought of.

209
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:54,390
He wants to guide the newcomers
as a veteran.

210
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:57,190
He wants more people to know about
the new authors.

211
00:12:57,990 --> 00:12:58,550
By the way,

212
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,990
all of your articles

213
00:13:00,990 --> 00:13:02,660
were specially picked by me.

214
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:03,870
What do you think?
I did a good job, right?

215
00:13:04,070 --> 00:13:05,550
I have nothing to fear when you're here.

216
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:07,870
By the way,

217
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,350
I've rewritten the ending for

218
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:11,070
The Disappearing Amusement Park.

219
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:13,070
Are you free tomorrow night?

220
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:14,190
I wish to discuss it with you.

221
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:16,910
Of course. You wrote another ending to it?

222
00:13:16,910 --> 00:13:19,030
Mr Jiang, you're really amazing.

223
00:13:19,350 --> 00:13:21,390
So, am I the first reader

224
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:22,630
of this new ending?

225
00:13:23,780 --> 00:13:26,350
Please remember to send the location
and time to me.

226
00:13:26,350 --> 00:13:27,550
I need to leave now.

227
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:28,670
I have a meeting to attend to.

228
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:29,470
Alright.

229
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:30,550
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

230
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:40,590
Hello?

231
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:43,260
Please reserve two spots
with the best view for me.

232
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:44,510
For two.

233
00:13:44,830 --> 00:13:47,270
For the Interactive Cultural Festival,

234
00:13:47,990 --> 00:13:49,630
no matter it's from the entries

235
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:51,430
or the response of the readers,

236
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:52,910
they're the best we've achieved
for the past two years.

237
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:56,430
We need to thank our leader for this.

238
00:13:56,430 --> 00:13:59,350
He has been fully supporting us for this.

239
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:03,550
But, there are some problems
regarding the festival as well.

240
00:14:04,470 --> 00:14:05,670
For the authors,

241
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:08,190
their popularity vary greatly.

242
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:09,310
Everyone knows that

243
00:14:09,310 --> 00:14:12,150
the current publishing field

244
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,390
isn't doing too well.

245
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:15,550
I think we can use this chance

246
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:17,470
to cut down on our number of authors.

247
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,750
All of the authors included

248
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:24,070
have a sturdy fanbase.

249
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:25,670
Their popularity

250
00:14:25,670 --> 00:14:27,270
is largely determined by the situation.

251
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:30,830
For example, for Mr Zhou Chuan
and Mr Jiang Yu Cheng

252
00:14:30,830 --> 00:14:33,030
Their fans are more active

253
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,590
on social media.

254
00:14:34,590 --> 00:14:37,430
That's why they may seem more popular.

255
00:14:37,430 --> 00:14:38,590
But for some authors,

256
00:14:38,590 --> 00:14:40,460
their readers are more mature.

257
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:41,870
They keep a low profile as well.

258
00:14:41,870 --> 00:14:43,950
Although they may not express themselves
on social media,

259
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,390
it doesn't mean that the authors
are not popular.

260
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:47,830
You're saying that they're popular?

261
00:14:47,950 --> 00:14:49,910
If that's so, why are people

262
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:51,510
faking data for them

263
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:52,590
behind the scenes?

264
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:57,070
Chief Editor Yu,

265
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,270
I'm sure you know who I'm talking about.

266
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:00,630
It's Suo Heng.

267
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:05,070
Everyone knows the amount of letter

268
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:09,150
Suo Heng had received this time,
am I right?

269
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:10,470
Five letters in total.

270
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:13,580
According to our data,

271
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,830
why is the second section

272
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:18,470
keeping an unpopular author like her?

273
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:21,150
Do you think she's our mascot?

274
00:15:22,230 --> 00:15:23,230
Mr Liang,

275
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:26,230
Ms Suo Heng has been writing
for Moonlight Magazine for a decade.

276
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:27,430
You can't just judge her capability

277
00:15:27,430 --> 00:15:29,790
based on an activity like this.

278
00:15:35,030 --> 00:15:37,150
Actually, the managing editor

279
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:39,270
has been reminding
Ms Suo Heng of her situation.

280
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:41,390
It's just that the results
aren't that positive.

281
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,110
You guys are seeing it for yourselves.

282
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:49,780
I was the one who brought Suo Heng
to our publishing house.

283
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:52,310
It's heartbreaking

284
00:15:52,630 --> 00:15:54,740
for me to say this,

285
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:56,190
but I have to say it

286
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,190
for the sake of the publishing house.

287
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:00,990
In my opinion,

288
00:16:01,310 --> 00:16:03,390
we should fire

289
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:04,910
unpopular authors like her.

290
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:07,110
We should leave spaces

291
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:09,670
for authors who are more worthy.

292
00:16:11,990 --> 00:16:14,030
This is a publishing house.

293
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:16,070
We aren't doing charity over here.

294
00:16:16,070 --> 00:16:18,470
There's no need for us to support

295
00:16:18,470 --> 00:16:20,550
the losers in life,

296
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:21,630
am I right?

297
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:22,900
Losers?

298
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:23,990
Miao,

299
00:16:23,990 --> 00:16:26,070
you think this has
nothing to do with you at all?

300
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:27,790
Chief Editor Yu,

301
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:29,310
we are in a meeting, you know?

302
00:16:29,310 --> 00:16:31,750
There's no need for you to
confront me directly.

303
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:34,190
Unpopular authors like Suo Heng
should've been

304
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:35,780
eliminated long ago.

305
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:38,630
It's been so many years, you know?
Do you think other publishing houses

306
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:40,790
are still publishing her works?

307
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:42,990
If it weren't for your support,

308
00:16:42,990 --> 00:16:44,750
she wouldn't have been able to stay with

309
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:46,310
Yuan Yue Publishing House
for so many years.

310
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:46,830
Miao.

311
00:16:46,830 --> 00:16:47,910
Chief Editor Yu,

312
00:16:48,510 --> 00:16:51,350
I know you've been asking other people
to write Suo Heng's stories for her.

313
00:16:51,350 --> 00:16:52,710
Director Yang was unhappy

314
00:16:52,710 --> 00:16:54,390
when he found out about it.

315
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,830
I tried my best to defend you, you know?

316
00:16:56,830 --> 00:16:59,510
Yet, you're still unwilling to give up?

317
00:16:59,830 --> 00:17:02,510
That's it. It's decided then.

318
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:04,390
If anyone has objections,

319
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:05,820
you can complain to Director Yang.

320
00:17:21,950 --> 00:17:23,420
Sir,

321
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:27,190
I've prepared steam rice rolls with
BBQ pork for your lunch.

322
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:29,390
Steam rice rolls with BBQ pork?

323
00:17:31,339 --> 00:17:32,190
Where is it?

324
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:33,910
Er Gou!

325
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:47,230
You're complaining to me about Er Gou?

326
00:17:49,390 --> 00:17:50,990
Come back home immediately

327
00:17:50,990 --> 00:17:52,670
and prepare another set
of steamed rice rolls for me.

328
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:56,100
Brother, can't you
please call for deliveries

329
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,420
using your phone?

330
00:17:58,030 --> 00:18:00,350
Why do you sound so down?

331
00:18:00,990 --> 00:18:02,470
I'll hang up now. Bye.

332
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:06,950
Chu Li, Ms Suo Heng

333
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:08,630
looks pale.

334
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:11,430
I feel like she's going
to faint at any time.

335
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:14,110
Fine.

336
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:15,900
Both of you are trying to
make me angry, huh?

337
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:17,710
You won't get to eat your favourite
chicken meatballs,

338
00:18:17,710 --> 00:18:18,590
you hear me?

339
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:27,270
Don't tell me she realized that

340
00:18:27,270 --> 00:18:29,190
I was Mr Fox after last night?

341
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:34,150
Mr Fox didn't reply her the entire night.

342
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:35,110
That won't do.

343
00:18:38,990 --> 00:18:40,390
How should I reply her?

344
00:18:42,590 --> 00:18:46,370
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

345
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:46,350
What are you doing?

346
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:47,350
No.

347
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:49,190
This sounds just like me.

348
00:18:55,530 --> 00:19:05,470
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

349
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:01,150
Good morning.

350
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:05,430
Today will be a great day.

351
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:11,550
Let's see if you still suspect me
as Mr Fox after this.

352
00:19:13,990 --> 00:19:15,350
Deputy Editor Miao.

353
00:19:16,470 --> 00:19:18,230
You must be kidding me, right?

354
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:20,070
Yuan Yue Publishing House and I

355
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:22,710
have been working together
for so many years.

356
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:25,790
How could you terminate
my contract just like that?

357
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,500
We had no choice.

358
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:33,110
We tried to fight for you,

359
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:34,430
but

360
00:19:34,790 --> 00:19:36,790
this is a decision made by the higher-ups.

361
00:19:36,790 --> 00:19:38,300
We didn't want this to happen either.

362
00:19:43,910 --> 00:19:46,110
Deputy Editor Miao, look.

363
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:49,300
I still have more than
10 types of novels with me.

364
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,590
I've completed everything

365
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:51,790
you asked of me.

366
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:53,500
I was always trying to be creative.

367
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,190
I'm not lying.

368
00:19:54,190 --> 00:19:55,470
I tried my best to be creative.

369
00:19:55,580 --> 00:19:56,950
Please take a look at them.

370
00:19:56,950 --> 00:19:59,030
Or I can write anything

371
00:19:59,030 --> 00:20:00,630
you guys ask of me.

372
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:03,060
As long as you guys don't give up on me.

373
00:20:05,870 --> 00:20:07,030
Suo Heng,

374
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:09,150
didn't I tell you already?

375
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,150
Regarding these scripts,

376
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:12,860
since we've worked together

377
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:15,030
for so many years,

378
00:20:15,230 --> 00:20:16,910
let me

379
00:20:16,910 --> 00:20:19,900
be honest with you.

380
00:20:20,150 --> 00:20:21,100
You're not suitable

381
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:23,420
for writing.

382
00:20:24,070 --> 00:20:26,870
It's better for you to find another job.

383
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:31,190
He said he's being honest with her?

384
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:33,310
He's stabbing Ms Suo Heng's gentle heart

385
00:20:33,310 --> 00:20:36,350
with a spear.

386
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:43,270
I've spent the most precious decade
of my life

387
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:45,030
on writing.

388
00:20:45,630 --> 00:20:46,950
I try my best

389
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:49,190
to write every day.

390
00:20:50,430 --> 00:20:53,270
I was thinking that even if
I wasn't talented as a writer,

391
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,550
my hard work will be able to
compensate for my lack of talent.

392
00:20:56,950 --> 00:20:58,390
I don't want my career to end like this.

393
00:20:58,390 --> 00:20:59,670
I can't accept this.

394
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:02,230
You can't accept this?

395
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:04,460
Even so, you can't just let
Yuan Yue Publishing House

396
00:21:04,460 --> 00:21:06,430
incur losses because of your stubbornness.

397
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,710
I understand now.

398
00:21:17,030 --> 00:21:17,780
I understand everything.

399
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:20,030
Great, I'm glad that you understood me.

400
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:22,990
Let's part with a smile then.

401
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,750
Just sign

402
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:26,350
on this contract.

403
00:21:26,580 --> 00:21:27,270
And that'll be all.

404
00:21:33,150 --> 00:21:34,470
I can't accept this!

405
00:21:35,590 --> 00:21:37,510
Miao, you better don't be too much!

406
00:21:37,510 --> 00:21:39,190
Aren't you being too anxious?

407
00:21:39,190 --> 00:21:40,030
Why are you here?

408
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:41,470
You have no say in this matter!

409
00:21:42,790 --> 00:21:44,870
Ms Suo Heng's novels

410
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:46,870
were great.

411
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:47,910
Every writer has their own style

412
00:21:47,910 --> 00:21:49,870
and themes they're good at.

413
00:21:49,870 --> 00:21:51,550
Things wouldn't have ended like this

414
00:21:51,550 --> 00:21:53,230
if you didn't force her
to change her style.

415
00:21:53,230 --> 00:21:54,830
I forced her to change her style?

416
00:21:55,390 --> 00:21:56,790
Tell me, should all writers

417
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,470
stay in their comfort zone then?

418
00:21:58,470 --> 00:22:00,270
I just wanted her to make a breakthrough.

419
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:01,390
But she couldn't make it.

420
00:22:01,390 --> 00:22:02,910
How could you blame this on me?

421
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:04,950
Is asking her to write something
she isn't good at

422
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:06,510
an attempt for her to make a breakthrough?

423
00:22:06,510 --> 00:22:07,870
If you love to help her out so much,

424
00:22:07,870 --> 00:22:09,110
why don't you write it for her then?

425
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:10,150
Enough!

426
00:22:16,510 --> 00:22:19,020
[Party B's signature]

427
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,340
[Yuan Yue Publishing House's
Termination Agreement]

428
00:22:27,550 --> 00:22:28,990
Actually, I know everything
that's been going on.

429
00:22:30,630 --> 00:22:32,390
I do read the private messages as well.

430
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:35,510
"Ms Suo Heng."

431
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:38,230
"Your writing is getting lousier."

432
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:40,550
"Ms Suo Heng."

433
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,550
"I miss the touching words

434
00:22:42,550 --> 00:22:44,470
you've written before."

435
00:22:45,310 --> 00:22:47,270
I know all of that.
I knew what was going on.

436
00:22:47,270 --> 00:22:49,420
I don't need you guys to take pity on me!

437
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,190
I don't need you guys to kick me around

438
00:22:54,190 --> 00:22:55,310
like a ball.

439
00:22:56,070 --> 00:22:57,110
Changing my editors

440
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:58,590
one after another.

441
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,670
Suo Heng,

442
00:23:01,670 --> 00:23:03,590
you can take back your scripts.

443
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,590
Just throw them away.

444
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:07,190
Ms Suo Heng.

445
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:10,790
Suo Heng!

446
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:11,540
Suo Heng.

447
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:15,470
Listen to me.

448
00:23:15,590 --> 00:23:17,030
You don't need to say anything.

449
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:17,910
I don't want to hear

450
00:23:17,910 --> 00:23:19,710
how unpopular I am anymore.

451
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:22,790
Wait for me.

452
00:23:22,790 --> 00:23:24,070
I'm sure there's a solution to this.

453
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:25,350
You've already forsaken me.

454
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:27,390
What's the meaning of this conversation?

455
00:23:29,990 --> 00:23:31,110
I can only say that

456
00:23:31,630 --> 00:23:32,990
I really had no choice back then.

457
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:34,790
That's why I told you

458
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:36,670
to find other editors.

459
00:23:36,670 --> 00:23:38,500
That's why I chose Miao.

460
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:43,830
I've signed the contract
of termination just now.

461
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:47,110
From now on,
you don't need to care about me.

462
00:24:15,530 --> 00:24:17,420
[The Best New Writer Award]

463
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:21,590
"This year's most unforgettable novel,

464
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:24,510
Golden Spears and Armoured Horses,

465
00:24:25,150 --> 00:24:27,310
a fantastic novel about the female gender,

466
00:24:27,310 --> 00:24:28,670
its author

467
00:24:28,670 --> 00:24:31,710
is a relatively unknown
and young female author."

468
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:32,830
Is she referring to me?

469
00:24:32,830 --> 00:24:33,940
-Yeah.
-Let me take a look!

470
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:35,470
Wait, there's more.

471
00:24:36,230 --> 00:24:36,870
Look.

472
00:24:37,710 --> 00:24:40,830
"This novel is just like a black horse,

473
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:43,350
crowning itself as
the top-selling novel of the year!"

474
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:46,270
"Crowned as the best novel of the year,

475
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:48,110
readers can expect great things

476
00:24:48,110 --> 00:24:50,230
from this up-and-coming author."

477
00:24:51,030 --> 00:24:52,030
We've made it.

478
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:53,070
Yeah.

479
00:24:53,070 --> 00:24:54,630
We've made it!

480
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:10,030
Hello?

481
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:12,590
[Are you Su Heng?]

482
00:25:14,030 --> 00:25:15,710
I am. Do you need anything from me?

483
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:17,590
[It's really you?]

484
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:19,310
[I'm Xu Chao from the literature club.]

485
00:25:19,310 --> 00:25:21,470
[I've been trying to contact you
for a long time.]

486
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:23,190
[Yu Yao did tell you that]

487
00:25:23,190 --> 00:25:25,710
[the literature club will
have a gathering tonight, right?]

488
00:25:25,910 --> 00:25:27,270
[You will attend the gathering, right?]

489
00:25:41,350 --> 00:25:42,550
Mr Zhou Chuan?

490
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:44,510
Why are you so childish?

491
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:47,310
You're pulling my braids just like
a primary student would.

492
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:49,190
Do you know how long
I've been waiting for you?

493
00:25:49,910 --> 00:25:52,030
I thought your lunch break is at 12 noon?

494
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:53,190
It's 1 p.m. now, you know?

495
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:56,350
Do we have an appointment
in the afternoon?

496
00:25:56,350 --> 00:25:57,590
Why don't I remember anything?

497
00:25:58,470 --> 00:26:00,310
I want steamed rice rolls with BBQ pork.

498
00:26:00,910 --> 00:26:01,750
And I had to wait for you.

499
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:02,870
You'll foot the bill later.

500
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:06,230
You look so down.

501
00:26:06,910 --> 00:26:07,870
What's wrong?

502
00:26:09,870 --> 00:26:12,310
It's all because of Ms Suo Heng.

503
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:15,870
She received too less replies from
the Interactive Cultural Festival.

504
00:26:15,870 --> 00:26:17,750
That's why Director Yang
is terminating her contract.

505
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:20,460
Even if Suo Heng couldn't make it,

506
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:21,990
Yu Yao is still there for her.

507
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:23,470
Why are you worried about her?

508
00:26:24,230 --> 00:26:26,790
Even you know her relationship
with Chief Editor Yu?

509
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:28,870
I know a little bit.

510
00:26:29,950 --> 00:26:31,070
Isn't Ms Suo Heng pitiful

511
00:26:31,070 --> 00:26:32,910
if Chief Editor Yu

512
00:26:32,910 --> 00:26:34,830
were to ignore her as well?

513
00:26:35,950 --> 00:26:38,310
So, what has this got to do with you?

514
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:40,190
Why has it got nothing to do with me?

515
00:26:40,990 --> 00:26:43,670
Miao said so before.
Even you are saying the same thing.

516
00:26:43,670 --> 00:26:45,390
But I'm an editor.

517
00:26:45,670 --> 00:26:46,990
As an editor,

518
00:26:46,990 --> 00:26:48,430
how could I watch and do nothing

519
00:26:48,430 --> 00:26:50,400
as a talented writer

520
00:26:50,630 --> 00:26:53,430
fades away?

521
00:26:53,990 --> 00:26:55,750
This concerns my professionalism.

522
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:58,070
If I failed after I've done my best,

523
00:26:58,070 --> 00:26:59,990
I won't say anything.

524
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:02,070
But if I keep quiet about it

525
00:27:02,070 --> 00:27:04,460
and pretend to be ignorant
because it doesn't concern me,

526
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:06,430
I will never be able to forgive myself.

527
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:08,390
As long as I'm working as an editor,

528
00:27:08,390 --> 00:27:10,470
I will never give up on any author.

529
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:12,270
That's why I became an editor
in the first place.

530
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:14,390
What if, one day,

531
00:27:14,390 --> 00:27:15,910
I run out of ideas?

532
00:27:15,910 --> 00:27:17,470
I will never give up on you as well.

533
00:27:17,470 --> 00:27:19,100
Incorrect. You should've said,

534
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:20,590
"Mr Zhou Chuan, it's impossible for you

535
00:27:20,590 --> 00:27:22,310
to run out of ideas?"

536
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:27,340
So,

537
00:27:27,340 --> 00:27:29,710
the talented, handsome,

538
00:27:29,710 --> 00:27:32,550
and resourceful Mr Zhou Chuan,

539
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:35,430
do you know where
Ms Suo Heng is staying at?

540
00:27:37,630 --> 00:27:39,150
You think I'm the paparazzi?

541
00:27:39,340 --> 00:27:40,220
Let's go.

542
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:46,430
What are you doing?

543
00:27:46,430 --> 00:27:48,030
